parameters.definition: Minutes required to shape one thin jar
Minutes required to bake one thin jar
Minutes required to shape one stubby jar
Minutes required to bake one stubby jar
Total available shaping minutes per week
Total available baking minutes per week

description: An artisan makes two types of terracotta jars: a thin jar and a stubby jar. Each thin jar requires \param{ThinShapingTime} minutes of shaping time and \param{ThinBakingTime} minutes of baking time. Each stubby jar requires \param{StubbyShapingTime} minutes of shaping time and \param{StubbyBakingTime} minutes of baking time. Per week, there are \param{TotalShapingTime} minutes available for shaping and \param{TotalBakingTime} minutes available for baking. The profit per thin jar is \param{ProfitThin} and the profit per stubby jar is \param{ProfitStubby}. How many jars of each type should the artisan make to maximize profit?
